<br>
(Silent Warrior) Right on about naked in the jungle, we didn't wear skivvies because we used them to clean our weapons; Barry didn't wear them because he liked the draft in between his legs.<br><br>
We did have a Marine that liked to lay around naked in his bunker all day long.  One day the Sgt. came by told him to go see the Captain and he got up that way and was going to go as he was. <br>
&quot;For Pete's sake, put on some clothes.&quot; The Sgt. told him. He put on, only a shirt and his Ho Chi Minh Sandals and went to see the CO that way.   REAL STORY!<br><br>
Hippies?<br>
Marty my A-gunner after he came home, became a hippie, <br>
&quot;Long hair freaky people, need not apply,&quot; the whole works, <br>
Today, he won't have a gun in his place. Abe well, he has them all over the place.<br>
I keep the M-60 pointed at the door for JW's, Mormons, Army recruiters and any boys that might want to come and ask my daughters out.<br><br>
I would send Barry a pair of real sandals, &quot;Ho Chi Minh sandals&quot; but then he would want to know where and how I got them. <br>
The entry bullet hole through the bottom of the left foot might reveal what the guy wearing them was doing when I opened up. I think it was just a little past curfew. NOT A REAL STORY!<br><br>
To Shrink-4-U<br>
&quot;That's all OK. I know where I have been, where I am, but not where I am going. And ya know? That's ok too.&quot; <br>
Awesome! There's that old question, WHERE ARE WE ALL GOING? Spatz, you little commie now you got me thinking, will need to check the gun's gas-cylinder, sometimes it gets plugged up with carbon when you've held the trigger down too long. Sometimes the barrel gets melted that way, need to let up. You got me thinking. Will let the gun cool and reexamine what the options are. <br><br>

